                <summary>The paper lists a number of crimes near Waynesboro. The store of Mr. Logan
                    at Fishersville was broken into and $300 worth of goods stolen. Thirty gallons
                    of apple brandy were stolen from the distillery of John Crouse on Simon Koiner's
                    farm. Thieves stole a number of clothing items from Charles Haines's store, and
                    food and utensils from the apartment of widow Wright.</summary>
                <note/>
